history.content:
162 is harder and more work. Both are fun if you enjoy systems and very educational, 161 is a bit more 'fun' fun since you get to do some real hacking.

For applicability to general SDE, I say slight-medium edge to 162 (others may disagree). 161 teaches lots of useful security concepts which is important in SDE, but 162 greatly matures your understanding of the OS and related topics (I/O, performance, etc), which is useful because most code in existence runs on an operating system.
